verse_part: and he hath sent him away,
shall I be had in honour.
for a great while to come.
and according to thine own heart,
and let us play the men
When thou hast made an end
And it came to pass, while
as soon as he had made an end
feign thyself to be a mourner,
and I would do him justice!
in a place that was far off.
And it came to pass, that
and it will come to pass,
And when he was come near
and we will hang them up
them that rose up against me
hast lifted me up on high
above them that rose up against me:
I will give thanks unto thee,
that one would give me drink
of that which doth cost me nothing.
